                        p.lead.mb-0(style="margin-top:4rem; padding:1rem") Unity’s HDRP delivers high quality renders in real time with current generation hardware. The HDRP uses physically based rendering. Many of the graphical calculations relating to light reflection and texture are precalculated. Once the calculations are done the information is baked into image files. Then the GPU can produce beautiful renders at the cost of a larger file size. 

